Document: StyleBoxLine  
Path: godot/classes/class_styleboxline.rst  
Summary: A StyleBox that displays a single horizontal or vertical line of specified color and thickness, used for separators.  

A StyleBox that displays a single line of a given color and thickness. The line can be either horizontal or vertical. Useful for separators.
---CHUNK---
Document: StyleBoxLine
Path: godot/classes/class_styleboxline.rst
Summary: Overview of StyleBoxLine class properties and their default values.

- color (Color): The color of the line. Default: Color(0, 0, 0, 1)
- grow_begin (float): Amount of padding at the beginning of the line. Default: 1.0
- grow_end (float): Amount of padding at the end of the line. Default: 1.0
- thickness (int): Thickness of the line in pixels. Default: 1
- vertical (bool): If true, the line is drawn vertically. Default: false
